@jeepers81: arggghhh.... :-)

You know, 1080p means the width of the video is 1920 pixels. The naming is a bit confusing... If the movie has 16:9 aspect ratio, it can be either 1.77:1, 1.85:1 or 2.39:1. Depending on the aspect ratio the height of the movie varies from 1080 to 800 (or so). The bottom line is: if you see a movie with a width of 1920 pixels, it IS "1080p" indeed.

Same applies to 720p: if the width is 1280, we call it 720p, no matter the real height.... I hope I could clear up the confusion! :-)

